reviews: I own shirts like this from Gildan, Fruit of the Loom and Hanes. I own several from each manufacturer. In general, the Fruit of the Loom are softer, the cuffs of Hanes are tighter (which I like), and the cuffs of the Gildan shirts seem to stretch out more quickly than the other two (which I don't like). The quality of fabric of all three seems OK to me, they all seem to wash equally well. If I needed another shirt of this kind, and my size was available, and the price differences weren't substantial, I would buy Fruit of the Loom first, Hanes second and Gildan as a third choice. The Gildan would not be my preferred choice but it would be acceptable.

reviews: Firstly, they fit perfectly. The quality is good too. My problem with it is the fabric. Being someone who lives with two long haired cats, one long haired dog, and a very sheddy family ... this sucks for me. The fit is great though and the value for money is great too, but it's not the most comfortable shirt I've ever worn and it's not well suited as an undershirt.

review_title: These are better value than others in the price range.
reviews: I purchased Gildan, Fruit of the Loom, Jazees and Russell long sleeve T-shirts all at the same time from Amazon. I also purchased George brand from WalMart. All have been laundered 3 or 4 or more times. The Gildan branded shirts are heavier weight material than the others. All except George have knitted cuffs and a taped neck band. George does not have knitted cuffs. The Fruit, Jazees and Russell shirts are lighter weight and fit a little smaller. The fruit have a narrow neck band and are rather short-wasted. The Jazees and Russell shirts were nice enough but not price competitive. The George shirts were in the same price range as the Fruit and Gildan shirts but were very short-wasted and inferior to the others in both material and finish.
